Honestly, I couldn't get through this article. It was bland and boring at best, so I skimmed it. I don't like that this opens with Dante literalism, especially when you state it in such a boring way. Have some teeth in your writing. Don't go halfway with this  either make it literally Hell or don't make it Hell at all.

There's a dozen quibbles I have to make over specific clauses and phrases, many of which are awkward as the result of needlessly inserted words. Take for instance, the following (which is but an example):



Demonic entities present within SCP-5660 are repelled when one of the 7 ideals of Christian sins are confessed to or performed near SCP-5660 with intent to repent.
附加记录：    

Your first problem is the needless  hurts the demons? I don't get the logic there.

I hate the dialogue. It's too far, far, too jocular for professionals, especially when one of these professionals is the Pope attempting to kill Satan. You're playing this for wackiness, and it just doesn't work.

The final major problem I have is that  the plan just doesn't make sense. The Pope occasionally takes confessional, yes, but it's not common. And even if he's appearing in public more often, people aren't generally confessing their sins to him? Are people just screaming their sins as Francis drives by in the Popemobile?



Coordinated efforts with other religions to attempt to confess sins and draw a clear boundary between confession and conversion
附加记录：    

A plan that starts with getting Protestants to go to confessional can only be described as absurd. And it then continues with getting non-Abrahamic faiths to confess Christian sins?








